EIB Aims to Cut Lending Toward Pre-Crisis Level, Tribune Says

-- B y   A l a n   K a t z
-- 
2011-02-23T07:31:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/eib-aims-to-cut-lending-toward-pre-crisis-level-tribune-says.html
The  European Investment Bank  wants
to gradually reduce lending to pre-financial-crisis levels,
daily  La Tribune  reported, citing EIB President Philippe
Maystadt.  The EIB signed loan agreements for 46 billion euros in 2006
and for 48 billion euros ($66 billion) in 2007, the newspaper
showed in a chart. By comparison, the bank signed agreements for
loans of 79 billion euros in 2009 and for 72 billion euros in
2010, according to the newspaper.  The EIB provides funding for projects such as road and
power-plant construction in  Europe , as well as for development
projects in poor regions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Katz in Paris at 
 akatz5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
